</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,2029,2092]" lastBlockId="9.[136,1452,158,473]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="170" pageId="8" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,388,2029,2055]" pageId="8" pageNumber="169">Vegetative structure:</emphasis>
—Thalli were purple-red, 
<quantity box="[691,818,2029,2056]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="169" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.2 cm</quantity>
high (
<figureCitation box="[896,981,2029,2056]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,929,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-292@8.[170,1416,929,1864]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Vegetative features of Gelidium sanyaense from Mexico. A–B. Thallus (FCME 10892). Scale = 0.2 mm. C. Apical cell (AP). Scale = 50 µm. D. Transvers section of erect branch with internal rhizoidal filaments (RHI). Scale = 40 µm. E. Enlargement of Fig. 5D. Scale = 25 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5751339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5751339/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="169">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
). The prostrate stolons were terete, erect axes upward and compact short brush-like haptera. The erect axes were compressed, percurrent and lanceolate, with a width of 190–320 µm. Thalli had simple or one to two orders irregularly branches. It has a rounded apical cell (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,929,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-292@8.[170,1416,929,1864]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Vegetative features of Gelidium sanyaense from Mexico. A–B. Thallus (FCME 10892). Scale = 0.2 mm. C. Apical cell (AP). Scale = 50 µm. D. Transvers section of erect branch with internal rhizoidal filaments (RHI). Scale = 40 µm. E. Enlargement of Fig. 5D. Scale = 25 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5751339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5751339/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="170">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
). Cross-sections of the main axes showed a fusiform outline, consisting of 2–3 layers of cortical cells and 3 layers of medullar cells (
<figureCitation box="[342,453,230,257]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,929,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-292@8.[170,1416,929,1864]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Vegetative features of Gelidium sanyaense from Mexico. A–B. Thallus (FCME 10892). Scale = 0.2 mm. C. Apical cell (AP). Scale = 50 µm. D. Transvers section of erect branch with internal rhizoidal filaments (RHI). Scale = 40 µm. E. Enlargement of Fig. 5D. Scale = 25 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5751339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5751339/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="170">Fig. 5c–d</figureCitation>
). Cortical cells were round 5–9.5 µm in width and medullary cells were elliptical 12–15 µm in width. Internal rhizoidal filaments abundant in the medulla. Reproductive structures not found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
